      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, a scaffolding checklist! A very sensible request, though I must say, if you're asking about scaffolding, you're already in the right mindset because I've seen too many projects go sideways when the little goblins get too close to the big metal tubes. Here is your quick pre-climb checklist, but keep in mind that every single bolt and bracket is a potential goblin trap if you aren't vigilant.\n\n**1. Foundation & Base Plates**\n*   **Check:** Are the base plates sitting on solid, level ground?\n*   **Goblin Note:** If the ground is soft or uneven, the goblins will start digging their claws into the concrete and the whole tower will wobble like a drunk goblin trying to stand on one leg. Make sure the mud is packed tight or you'll have a very unhappy crew later.\n\n**2. Couplers & Connections**\n*   **Check:** Are all swivel, right-angle, and sleeve couplers tightened to the manufacturer's torque specs?\n*   **Goblin Note:** A loose coupler is just a goblin's favorite hiding spot. If one slips, it's like a goblin sneaking up behind you and biting your",
