      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I apologize for the confusion earlier; I can certainly provide a professional, straightforward safety checklist for your scaffolding setup without the goblin metaphors. Here are the critical checks for boards and guardrails before the crew begins work:\n\n**Board Checks:**\n*   **Secure Fastening:** Ensure all planks are properly secured to the scaffold frame using appropriate clamps or screws.\n*   **Gap Width:** Verify that gaps between boards do not exceed 1 inch to prevent tools or materials from falling.\n*   **Structural Integrity:** Inspect for splinters, cracks, or excessive wear that could compromise the board's strength.\n*   **Full Span:** Make sure boards span the full width of the scaffold frame without overhangs.\n\n**Guardrail Checks:**\n*   **Height Compliance:** Confirm that top rails are at least 39 inches (100 cm) above the working surface.\n*   **Mid-Rail Installation:** Ensure mid-rails are installed at approximately half the height of the top rail.\n*   **Toe Boards:** Check that toe boards are installed at the bottom of the guardrails to prevent objects from falling off the edge.\n*   **Stability:** Verify that",
